Musings =E2=80=A6 my thoughts, every day since March 20, 2003 =E2=80=A6
I always tell myself I want a well-made plan, not because I worship process=
 (but I have well-worn lessons to =E2=80=98trust process=E2=80=99 =E2=80=A6=
 somewhat equal to memories of times =E2=80=98trusting process=E2=80=99 fai=
led to stop something foolish =E2=80=A6) but because I=E2=80=99ve lived thr=
ough what happens when good intentions dress themselves up as structure and=
 ask not to be questioned.=20
Still, beginnings rarely arrive with perfect clarity.
Or on the day and time we marked on our calendar to =E2=80=98start _______=
=E2=80=99 =E2=80=A6
No, they arrive one day, like a planted seed/spore - they fester, germinate=
, percolate and grow like a fungus until, that fine day arrives - today - o=
n this Saturday morning, one on my desk along with countless other tasks ci=
rcling, and also in my mind =E2=80=A6 all those dusty, dry old bone-rattlin=
g ideas in drawers in my mind, and just enough belief to make abandoning th=
e idea/project something we can=E2=80=99t do. So, the time to begin this is=
 now; not all the previous =E2=80=98maybe now=E2=80=99 moments, but now. Ri=
ght now.
I=E2=80=99ve learned this before, in several very expensive ways.
Any project can be sincere, energetic, even admirable, and still leave behi=
nd a box of tax-deductible expense receipts, a thinner wallet, and not to m=
ention the lost sleep/opportunity/leisure time ~ and the kind of memories t=
hat become amusing only after much time has passed.=20
The worst is when you don=E2=80=99t learn much, or use the learning, after =
paying all that tuition =E2=80=A6
A boss/mentor once told me I could never live long enough to make all the m=
istakes myself, so I should learn from others' mistakes. Good advice, proba=
bly. But I=E2=80=99ve noticed that other people=E2=80=99s wreckage rarely t=
eaches me half as much as my own collisions with reality ...
Everybody knows this, don=E2=80=99t we?=20
We admire caution right up to the moment some idea gets hold of us and star=
ts acting like a summons to appear =E2=80=A6=20
So here I sit, in my office on a Saturday morning, with the clear plan/runw=
ay I planned, with way more interruptions in recent months than I thought I=
 might get through =E2=80=A6
=E2=80=A6. still, something I=E2=80=99m certain I want to begin.=20
Not blindly.
This is a re-start, but no replay.
Clearer goals, clearer steps, clearer understanding of who matters in it, w=
ho pays for it, who benefits from it, and whether I can explain it without =
sounding like I=E2=80=99m still explaining it to myself.
I=E2=80=99ve tried a version of this project before. It was well-intentione=
d, good-hearted and not especially successful.=20
Tom Peters words are tapping me on the shoulder once again:
ready, fire, aim
And somewhere behind this project, I can hear the dusty skeletons of long-g=
one but never forgotten blunders, many of them, waiting to ask for another =
turn.
Many might say an intricate checks/balances plan is what matters, but somet=
imes that evidence of a belief is rarely certainty - only that what serves =
us best and without fatigue, is the willingness/resolve to begin before tho=
se who doubt have finished clearing their throats.

